Disney Emoji Blitz is a featured article, which means it has been identified as one of the best articles produced by the Disney Wiki community. If you see a way this page can be updated or improved without compromising previous work, please feel free to contribute.

 

Disney Emoji Blitz

Developer

Disney Mobile (2016-2019)
Jam City (2019-present)

Publisher

Disney Mobile (2016-2019)
Jam City (2019-present)

Platform(s)

iOS, Android and Windows 10 Mobile

Released

July 14, 2016

Genre

Match 3
Source


Disney Emoji Blitz is a Match-3 game based on Emojis. It was released on July 14, 2016.

Synopsis

Match. Collect. Emote! Play and collect hundreds of Disney and Pixar emojis like never before in an exciting, calming matching game!

Play fast-paced rounds of match-3 to earn prizes, complete missions, and discover new emojis. Collect Disney and Pixar emoji characters and items from The Little Mermaid, The Lion King, Cinderella, Zootopia, The Muppets, Toy Story, Monsters, Inc., Finding Dory, and many more!

  • MATCH emojis to score big points and unlock new characters
  • COLLECT 400+ Disney and Pixar emoji characters and items
  • BLAST the board with expressive emoji superpowers and combos
  • PLAY missions to boost your score and earn prizes
  • CHALLENGE your friends' high scores
  • SHARE your collected emojis through the Emoji Blitz keyboard

Goals

  • Collect Emojis
  • Increase Mission Level
    • The current maximum Mission Level is Level 570.
  • Compete against friends for high score and food fights.
  • Complete Item Collections
    • For a complete list, see Disney Emoji Blitz item collections.
  • Complete Daily Challenges
    • Each day there are three challenges: Easy, Medium, and Hard, that upon completion gives the prize of a Bronze Chest, Silver Chest, and Gold Chest respectively.
    • The Daily Challenges are usually "Clear __ Emojis", "Use __ ", "Use __ ", "Use __ ", or combinations of these.

Boxes

Characters can be purchased from Silver Boxes (15,000 coins), Gold Boxes (30,000 coins), Series Boxes (30,000 coins) or Diamond Boxes (200 Gems). Some characters are exclusive to certain events. Silver Box characters can be upgraded to Power Level 3, Gold Box characters to Level 5, Villain Box characters to Level 5, and Story and Rainbow Box characters to either Level 1, Level 3 or Level 5.

Trivia

  • Thirty-seven characters have multiple versions of themselves available in the game.
    • Mickey has 8-Bit Mickey, Steamboat Willie Mickey, Holiday Mickey, Sorcerer's Apprentice Mickey, Rainbow Mickey, Vampire Mickey, Bob Cratchit Mickey, Deep Sea Mickey, Gardener Mickey, Ice Cream Mickey, Pumpkin Mickey, and Gingerbread Mickey.
    • Donald has Crab Donald, Caballero Donald, Royal Magician Donald, and Soft Serve Donald.
    • Pluto has Holiday Pluto and Birthday Baby Pluto.
    • Minnie has Retro Minnie, Holiday Minnie, Rose Gold Minnie, Witch Minnie, Mermaid Minnie, Fairy Minnie, Peppermint Minnie, Flower Minnie, and Watermelon Minnie.
    • Daisy has Seashell Daisy.
    • Goofy has Vacation Goofy, Ghost of Jacob Marley, Captain Goofy, and Sea Creature Goofy.
    • Scrooge McDuck has Ebenezer Scrooge McDuck.
    • Chip has Angel Chip.
    • Dale has Devil Dale.
    • Pooh has Honey Bee Pooh.
    • Piglet has Flower Piglet.
    • Tigger has Bunny Tigger.
    • Buzz has Mrs. Nesbit.
    • Dory has Baby Dory.
    • Belle has Winter Belle.
    • Beast has Fancy Beast.
    • Mulan has Ping.
    • Rapunzel has Tiara Rapunzel.
    • Jack Skellington has Santa Jack.
    • Sally has Christmas Sally.
    • Dante has Alebrije Dante.
    • Yzma has Yzma Kitty.
    • Simba has Baby Simba.
    • Jasmine has Disguised Jasmine.
    • Jafar has Snake Jafar.
    • Ariel has Wedding Ariel.
    • Cinderella has Wedding Cinderella.
    • Moana has Baby Moana.
    • Maximus has Wedding Maximus.
    • Genie has Vacation Genie.
    • Tiana has Almost There Tiana.
    • Dug has Headphones Dug.
    • Ursula has Vanessa.
    • Pegasus has Baby Pegasus.
    • Madam Mim has Young Mim.
    • Anna has Queen Anna.
    • Elsa has Elsa the Snow Queen.
      • Oddly enough, there are two characters that do not have a regular counterpart of themselves: Spirit Mufasa and Pirate Peg-Leg Pete.
      • Other variants of other characters have yet to be introduced (including Baloo and King Louie's TaleSpin renditions).
  • All twelve Disney Princesses are available in the game. In addition to this, some of the unofficial princesses (Princess Atta and Princess Leia) also count towards the 'Disney Princess' missions in the game, although others (Anna and Elsa) do not.
    • As of version 32.0.0, Anna no longer counts towards the 'Disney Princess' missions.
    • So far, Prince Eric, Aladdin, Prince Charming, The Beast, Flynn Rider, Prince Phillip and The Prince are the only Disney Princes to be playable characters in the game; however, Flynn Rider is the only one that does not count towards the 'Disney Prince' missions.
    • In version 29.0.0, the Princes Group Collection called for Flynn Rider instead of The Beast, but was reverted in version 29.1.0.
  • There are currently twenty-seven Disney Villains available in the game: Ursula, Maleficent, Jafar, Captain Hook, Scar, Shenzi, Cruella De Vil, The Queen of Hearts, Hades, The Evil Queen, Magica De Spell, Oogie Boogie, Gaston, Dr. Facilier, Madam Mim, Tamatoa, King Candy, Yzma, Shan Yu, Lucifer, Mother Gothel, Lady Tremaine, Pirate Peg-Leg Pete, Demona, Prince John, Madame Medusa, and Governor Ratcliffe.
    • Alpha, Zurg, Ernesto, Syndrome, and Lotso are the only Pixar Villains that have been added to the Villain Box.
  • There are currently five Muppets available in the game (Kermit, Fozzie, Swedish Chef, Miss Piggy, and Gonzo).
  • There are currently twenty-four Star Wars characters available in the game (Rey, Finn, BB-8, Poe Dameron, Luke Skywalker, Princess Leia, Chewbacca, Han Solo, R2-D2, The Mandalorian, Cara Dune, Hondo, The Child, Kylo Ren, Darth Vader, Stormtrooper, Moff Gideon, Death Trooper, Boba Fett, C-3PO, Jabba the Hutt, Anakin Skywalker, Queen Amidala and Darth Maul).
  • There are currently ten characters that originate from Disney Television Animation available in the game (Launchpad McQuack, Darkwing Duck, Webby, Gizmoduck, Monterey Jack, Gadget, Goliath, Demona, Bronx, and Angel).
    • Although The Adventures of the Gummi Bears and TaleSpin were the only Disney Afternoon shows to not have any characters yet (including the latter show's renditions of Baloo and King Louie), some of the items from these shows appear during said event.
  • There are currently seven characters that originate from the Disney parks (Hatbox Ghost, Hitchhiker Ghost Phineas, Abominable Snowman, Madame Leota, The Bride, Figment, and Prison Dog).
  • There are currently fifteen characters that originate from Disney live-action films (Captain Jack Sparrow, Barbossa, Davy Jones, Elizabeth Swann, Tia Dalma, Mal, Giselle, Frank, Dr. Lily Houghton, Winifred Sanderson, Mary Poppins, Bert, Mary Sanderson, Sarah Sanderson, and Billy Butcherson).
  • There are currently ten characters that do not fall into the Boy or Girl categories (Alien, Sugar Bowl, BB-8, R2-D2, C-3PO, Magic Carpet, The Fire Spirit, Ping, Stormtrooper, and Death Trooper).
    • There is also one character that falls into both categories (Mrs. Nesbit).
  • There are currently two characters that always appear on the board when playing as a specific emoji (Mike with Celia, and Simba with Spirit Mufasa).
  • There are currently two characters that originate from Disney video games (Sora and Aqua).
  • There are currently two characters that originate from the Donald Duck comics universe (Scrooge McDuck and Magica De Spell).
  • Out of all the Monsters, Inc. characters in the app, the app currently doesn't feature any characters introduced in Monsters University.
    • However, there are two items (MU Pennant and MU Jacket), both of which reference the pennants and the jackets seen in the film.
  • The screen that appears when using Jackson Storm's ability shows several numbers on the data screen in the order of "4-8-15-16-23-42", a set of numbers associated with mystery of the ABC television show Lost.
  • The Gold Boxes resemble ? Blocks from the Mario games.
